SIMPLE: uprise
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uprise
<hw>Up*rise"</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧p*r⟦imac⟧z")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To rise; to get up; to appear from below the
horizon.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Uprose</xex> the sun.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Cowley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Uprose</qex> the virgin with the morning light.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To have an upward direction or
inclination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Uprose</qex> the mystic mountain range.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uprise</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uprise
<hw>Up*rise"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of rising; appearance
above the horizon; rising.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Did ever raven sing so like a lark,⟦br⟧
That gives sweet tidings of the sun's <qex>uprise</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uprising</ent>⟦br⟧
